This paper is about face recognition using sparse representation and Bayesian learning. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of information theory (IT) and multimedia (MM) in the context of face recognition. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks (NE) as a benchmark for comparison. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.IT, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
